At 08:52 PM 5/13/2003, Billy wrote:
>Second failure in three years. What's going wrong?

Where is it breaking?  If in the bowden tube area, replace the bowden tube.  If damaged, it can cause the clutch cable to fail - happened to me a couple of years ago.  Fortunately, new bowden tubes are available for not too much money.

-David
